  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Liverpool Care Pathway for the dying patient (LCP) was developed to transfer the care
      practice from the hospice setting to the hospital setting in UK. LCP is a pathway with
      standardized registration method to monitor the care and its results. The primary aim is to
      study the effects of LCP on dying patients symptom burden and communication with close
      relatives and health care professionals.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      All residential care homes in Skellefteå municipality are included in the study and
      randomized either to control or intervention group. During the baseline period the care is
      provided as usual. During the intervention period the LCP is used for patients for whom the
      dying phase is diagnosed in the intervention group. Usual care is performed for the control
      group. After death of a patient a close relative fill in a questionnaire.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
